parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The corrosion or rust of the subframe can cause the vehicle to become unsafe to drive, leading to loss of control, accidents, or injuries.
symptoms: The vehicle may exhibit unusual noises
vibrations
or pulling to one side while driving. In severe cases
the subframe may break
causing the vehicle to become immobile.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the door handle chrome plating can cause sharp edges to be exposed, leading to lacerations or injuries to passengers.
symptoms: The chrome plating on the door handles may peel off
revealing sharp edges.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Other issues, such as heat shield failure, clutch master cylinder failure, and paint flaking, can cause inconvenience, discomfort, or safety risks to vehicle occupants.
symptoms: The heat shield may fall off
the clutch pedal may stick or feel soft
or the paint may flake off
causing unevenness or discoloration.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The corrosion and failure of the subframe can cause the vehicle to lose control, leading to accidents, injuries, and fatalities.
symptoms: The vehicle pulls to one side
the tire wears unevenly
the vehicle makes abnormal noises
the wheel collapses into the wheel well
the axle breaks
and the vehicle becomes difficult to control.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The rust and failure of the rear subframe can cause the vehicle to lose control, leading to accidents, injuries, and fatalities.
symptoms: The rear trailing arm breaks off
the vehicle swerves or loses control
the rear subframe rusts away
and the vehicle becomes difficult to control.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the front lower control arm can cause the vehicle to lose control, leading to accidents, injuries, and fatalities.
symptoms: The front lower control arm fractures
the vehicle pulls to one side
the tire wears unevenly
and the vehicle becomes difficult to control.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the airbag system can lead to the non-deployment of airbags in the event of an accident, resulting in serious injuries or fatalities.
symptoms: The airbag light stays on
the airbag deploys unexpectedly
the airbag does not deploy in an accident
the passenger side airbag sensor light illuminates constantly.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the PPD can cause the airbag light to stay on, indicating a problem with the airbag system, and potentially leading to the non-deployment of airbags in the event of an accident.
symptoms: The airbag light stays on
the PPD sensor is defective
the airbag system malfunctions.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the airbag wiring harness can cause the airbag system to malfunction, leading to the non-deployment of airbags in the event of an accident.
symptoms: The airbag light stays on
the airbag system malfunctions
the wiring harness is damaged.
